				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, I've been boxing my mage with a L65 cleric for a week or so now and have been using his epic pet to tank most mobs throughout this time. (epic DS + clerical reverse DS = 84 points of yum)  Anyway, when level 62 I'll have both the L61 air pet, L62 water pet available to me... along with our single target 48pt DS.  Is it time to switch to either the air pet or water pet for tanking in this duo?  Does the air pet mitigation compensate for the lesser hit points, and (possibly) lower DPS?
<br />

<br />
FWIW, I've been fighting mobs unslowed and relying on the DS + reverse DS for a great deal my DPS to this point.  I'll continue to use this tactic through L65 most likely, when I'll finally group the cleric with the mage and push both to L70.
<br />

<br />
I'll try the different combinations out myself later this week and let people know what my impressions are.  Just curious if anyone has tested something similar before.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
