				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Interesting...
<br />
I assume the ring drops in OoW.  Any word on which mob?
<br />

<br />
I've been putting off DPoC until I reached 65, largely beacuse of the point gathering rate at lower levels... and with the cleric in tow the extra umpfh in the pet is nice, but not critical.  Now I notice that with two runes at 66 we get a pet substantially better than any pre-65 pet focused with Summoner's Boon... and further that pet focusing seems not as impressive in the 66+ pets.
<br />

<br />
My plan had shifted to getting the 66 air pet first, then focusing on LDoN points for the DPoC... but if an attuneable item is available, or fiarly easy to acquire, well... that changes my plans yet again.
<br />

<br />
-- Edit --
<br />

<br />
As for a pet comparison... 
<br />

<br />
I tried PoI, PoJ, PoN and PoV over the last two nights with the Epic pet and WoX (neither focused).  While two boxing the epic pet was actually a bit better in PoI, PoJ and PoN in terms of experience acquisition per until time... but required periodic bouts of down time when the cleric went OoM.    WoX was slightly slower, but XP with virtually no down time in those areas.  In PoV it was WoX hands down.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
